## Rod Segments and Couplers {#sec-rod-segments}

## Rod Material Selection {#sec-material-selection}

Material selection is critical for probe performance. The rod must be non-conductive to avoid interference with electromagnetic measurements, strong enough to withstand insertion forces, and durable for repeated field use. Fiberglass (G10) emerges as the preferred material due to its combination of high strength, non-conductivity, RF transparency, and moderate cost.

::: {.cell fig-height='6' fig-width='10' execution_count=4}

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display}
![Material selection guide for probe rod construction. Fiberglass (G10) is the preferred material offering the best balance of strength, non-conductivity, and cost. Metal rods must be avoided as they interfere with electromagnetic measurements.](mechanical_files/figure-pdf/fig-material-specs-output-1.png){#fig-material-specs}
:::
:::


| Parameter | Specification |
|-----------|---------------|
| Outer Diameter (OD) | 16 mm (Target) (approx. 5/8") |
| Inner Diameter (ID) | 12-13 mm (Manufacturer spec) |
| Wall Thickness | ~1.5-2.0 mm (Manufacturer spec) |
| Material | Fiberglass (non-conductive, RF transparent) |
| Segment Lengths | 50 cm, 100 cm (Target) (spacers) |

: Fiberglass rod specifications. {#tbl-fiberglass}

## Modular Connector System {#sec-modular-connector}

The system uses a 2-part connector system permanently epoxied into rod ends to create a screw-together stack. The male insert provides the threaded portion while the female insert/sensor module receives the thread and houses sensors. This flush-mount design ensures a smooth 16mm OD (Target) profile throughout, preventing snag points during insertion and extraction.

::: {.cell fig-height='9' fig-width='10' execution_count=5}

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display}
![Modular flush-mount connector system showing (a) assembled view with smooth profile and (b) exploded view revealing male/female insert architecture. The 6mm (Target) central channel accommodates wiring. M12x1.75 (Manufacturer spec) threads provide robust mechanical connection.](mechanical_files/figure-pdf/fig-modular-connection-output-1.png){#fig-modular-connection}
:::
:::


## Thread Specifications {#sec-thread-specs}

All threaded connections use M12x1.75 ISO standard metric threads. This provides adequate strength for field assembly while remaining manufacturable via 3D printing with post-processing. The "chunky" thread profile improves printability while maintaining engagement strength.

::: {.cell fig-height='5' fig-width='10' execution_count=6}

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display}
![M12x1.75 thread profile detail showing (a) male thread external profile and (b) female thread cross-section. Pitch of 1.75mm (Manufacturer spec) provides good engagement with 12-15mm (Target) thread length. Male threads print at 12.2mm (Target) OD for die cutting; female threads print at 10.5mm (Target) ID for tapping.](mechanical_files/figure-pdf/fig-thread-detail-output-1.png){#fig-thread-detail}
:::
:::


| Parameter | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| Thread Type | M12x1.75 ISO Standard |
| Pitch | 1.75 mm (Manufacturer spec) |
| Major Diameter | 12.0 mm (Manufacturer spec) |
| Engagement Length | 12-15 mm (Target) |
| Print Oversize (Male) | 12.2 mm (Target) (for Die cutting) |
| Print Undersize (Female) | 10.5 mm hole (Target) (for Tapping) |

: Thread specifications for modular connections. {#tbl-thread}

## Coil Mounting and Ferrite Cores {#sec-coil-mounting}

The MIT sensing coils are wound onto ferrite rod cores positioned along the probe body. This configuration keeps coils internal to the 16mm (Target) profile, adding only 1-2mm (Target) to the rod OD with potting. Coils are positioned orthogonally (90 degree separation) to minimize direct coupling between TX and RX elements.

::: {.cell fig-height='6' fig-width='10' execution_count=7}

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display}
![Coil assembly detail showing ferrite rod core (100mm x 6mm) (Target) with copper wire windings (200-400 turns (Target) of 0.2mm (Target) enameled wire). Support brackets maintain alignment within the probe cavity. Lead wires route to the surface junction box.](mechanical_files/figure-pdf/fig-coil-mounting-output-1.png){#fig-coil-mounting}
:::
:::


| Parameter | Specification |
|-----------|---------------|
| Diameter | 6-8 mm (Target) |
| Length | 40-80 mm (Target) |
| Material | MnZn ferrite |
| Quantity | 1-2 per probe (TX/RX) |

