## ERT Ring Electrodes {#sec-mech-ert-rings}

Electrical Resistivity Tomography (ERT) electrodes are implemented as narrow stainless steel or copper ring bands mounted on 3D-printed insulating collars. The rings are flush-mounted to maintain the smooth probe profile. Multiple rings (typically 2-3 per probe) enable various measurement configurations.

::: {.cell fig-height='5' fig-width='10' execution_count=8}

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-display}
