### Troubleshooting Common Issues {#sec-proto-troubleshooting}

::: {.callout-note}
## No Signal on Oscilloscope

1. Check function generator output (probe directly)
2. Verify coil continuity with multimeter
3. Check all cable connections
4. Try higher drive voltage (up to 5V p-p)
:::

::: {.callout-note}
## No Response to Metal Target

1. Try larger target (bigger = stronger signal)
2. Try closer distance (<5cm (Target))
3. Try different frequencies (2, 5, 20, 50 kHz (Target))
4. Verify coil current is flowing (series resistor voltage)
5. Check for shorted turns (Q factor very low)
:::

::: {.callout-note}
## Threads Won't Fit

1. Chase with M12x1.75 tap (female) or die (male)
2. Light sanding on male thread OD
3. Check for debris or print defects
4. If cracking: reprint using blanks + tap/die approach
:::

